# Commits

Full guides: `docs/contributing/commits.md`, `docs/contributing/branches.md`

## Format (Conventional Commits, English)

```
<type>(<scope>): <short summary>

[optional body]

[optional footer]
```

**Types**: `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `test`, `docs`, `chore`, `ci`, `perf`, `build`

## Rules

- Subject ≤ 72 characters; imperative mood; English only
- One logical change per commit
- Never commit secrets (`.env`, credentials, keys)
- Never skip hooks (`--no-verify`) unless user explicitly requests
- Never amend pushed commits unless user explicitly requests
- Only create commits when the user asks

## Examples

```
feat(orders): add idempotent order creation endpoint

fix(auth): reject expired refresh tokens on rotation

test(inventory): cover insufficient stock rejection
```
